A federal judge allowed Tyco International Ltd. shareholders to proceed with a class-action lawsuit seeking damages against former executives and the company's auditor.
The retrial of L. Dennis Kozlowski and Mark Swartz involves charges of stealing $600 million.
Prosecutors focus on alleged thefts rather than extravagant purchases.
The case highlights corporate greed and financial manipulation.
Defense lawyers criticize former directors' credibility.
The trial showcases a narrative of illegal bonuses and hidden compensation.
